I have an Angular landing page. The current header is a static green 
bar (corporate green, part of Fidelity/CST brand standards) that looks 
completely disconnected from the dark hero below it.

Redesign the header component with Mammut-style scroll behavior:
- At page top: header is fully transparent, floats over the hero
- On scroll: header slides down from above with a dark frosted background
- Corporate green is RETAINED but used minimally as an accent only — 
  NOT as the background color

No external libraries. Vanilla TypeScript + CSS only.
Complete implementation — no stubs, no TODOs.

---

### The exact scroll behavior (Mammut pattern)

State 1 — AT TOP (scroll position = 0):
  - Header background: transparent
  - Header position: fixed, top: 0
  - Logo text color: #ffffff
  - Nav links color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75)
  - No border, no shadow
  - The hero content is fully visible beneath it

State 2 — SCROLLED (scroll position > 60px):
  - Header slides in: 
      transform: translateY(-100%) → translateY(0)
      transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)
      (this is the "slide down from above" feel — ease out expo curve)
  - Background: rgba(10, 13, 18, 0.92)
  - backdrop-filter: blur(12px) saturate(1.4)
    (frosted glass over the page content below)
  - Border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06)
  - Logo and nav text: #ffffff (full opacity)

State 3 — SCROLLING BACK UP to top:
  - When scroll returns below 60px, background fades back to transparent
  - transition: background 0.3s ease, backdrop-filter 0.3s ease
  - Do NOT slide out again — only the background fades, header stays fixed

